# Kconfig.projbuild for the ble_keyboard component
#
# Adding this component to an ESP-IDF project (with framework-espidf and
# the NimBLE host) auto-selects the options that the `esp_hid` component
# needs to compile the NimBLE backend of esp_hidd_dev_init.
#
# The relevant symbols are:
#   - esp_hid_dev_init (in esp_hid/src/esp_hidd.c) dispatches to either
#     esp_ble_hidd_dev_init (NimBLE backend in esp_hid/src/nimble_hidd.c)
#     or esp_bt_hidd_dev_init (Bluedroid backend in esp_hid/src/bt_hidd.c).
#   - The NimBLE implementation is gated by `CONFIG_BT_NIMBLE_HID_SERVICE`
#     in nimble_hidd.c itself: the entire body of esp_ble_hidd_dev_init
#     is wrapped in `#if CONFIG_BT_NIMBLE_HID_SERVICE`.
#   - The esp_hid component's CMakeLists.txt adds nimble_hidd.c to its
#     source list when `CONFIG_BT_NIMBLE_ENABLED` is set, but does NOT
#     enable the HID service itself; that has to be set by the user (or
#     by this Kconfig) explicitly.
#
# Without CONFIG_BT_NIMBLE_HID_SERVICE=y, the linker fails with:
#   undefined reference to `esp_ble_hidd_dev_init'
#
# This Kconfig lets the ble_keyboard component pull in the option it
# needs, the same way the esp_hid_device example does it
# (examples/bluetooth/esp_hid_device/main/Kconfig.projbuild).

menu "BLE Keyboard component"

    config BLE_KEYBOARD_ENABLED
        bool "Enable BLE Keyboard HID device"
        default y
        depends on BT_NIMBLE_ENABLED
        select BT_NIMBLE_HID_SERVICE
        help
            Enables the BLE Keyboard component. Selecting this option
            also auto-enables the NimBLE HID service so that the
            esp_hid device library has a NimBLE backend compiled in
            and the symbol `esp_ble_hidd_dev_init` is defined.

endmenu
